Many pundits questioned California’s decision to move our presidential primary election to an earlier date.
The fact that the winner of the California Democratic Primary did not become the party’s nominee has only served as fuel for the skepticism.
The Sacramento Bee tracked 458 campaign visits to the Golden State by Democratic candidates alone.
Sanders, who won the most votes in the California Democratic Primary, hosted mega-rallies in Northern and Southern California the weekend before Super Tuesday.
And more fundamental than the political implications of our earlier presidential primary, it was a compelling win for voter participation.